The '''FPS Public Health, Food Chain Safety and Environment''' ({{lang-nl|FOD Volksgezondheid, Veiligheid van de Voedselketen en Leefmilieu}}, {{lang-fr|SPF Santé publique, Sécurité de la Chaîne alimentaire et Environnement}}, {{lang-de|FÖD Volksgesundheit, Sicherheit der Nahrungsmittelkette und Umwelt}}), more commonly known as the '''FPS Health''', is a [[Federal Public Service]] of [[Belgium]]. It was created by [[Royal Order]] on May 23, 2001, as part of the plans of the [[Verhofstadt I Government]] to modernise the federal administration.
It is responsible for guaranteeing the [[public health]], the safety of the [[food chain]] and a safe [[Natural environment|environment]].
==Organisation== The FPS Health is currently organised into three Directorates-General and an Administration: *The Directorate-General for Health Care *The Directorate-General for Animals, Plants and Foodstuffs *The Directorate-General for Environment *The Administration of Medical Expertise (Medex)
The former Directorate-General for Medicinal Products has become the autonomous [[Federal Agency for Medicines and Health Products]] in 2007. The Directorate-General for Health Care is the result of the merger of the Directorate-General for Health Care Facilities Organisation and the Directorate-General for Primary Health Care & Crisis Management. The FPS Health is also linked with two [[Scientific institution|scientific institutions]]:
*[[Sciensano]], the successor to the former Center for Veterinary and Agrochemical Research and the former Scientific Institute of Public Health *The Superior Health Council
