 |publisher=[[Bloomberg News]]
}}</ref>
International Energy Agency (IEA) Ministerial meeting was held in Paris, France on 7 and 8 November 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.iea.org/newsroom/events/high-level-event-2017-iea-ministerial-meeting.html|title=Events: High-Level Event: 2017 IEA Ministerial Meeting|website=www.iea.org|access-date=2017-12-06}}</ref>

== Member states ==

Only the [[Organisation for Economic Co-operation and Development|OECD]] member states can become members of the IEA. Except for [[Chile]], [[Iceland]], [[Israel]], and [[Slovenia]], all OECD member states are members of the IEA. In 2014, Estonia joined the IEA and became its 29th member.<ref>[http://www.iea.org/countries/membercountries International Energy Agency membership list]</ref> Brazil, China, India, Indonesia, Morocco, Singapore and Thailand are the associate members of IEA. In 2018, Mexico joined the IEA and became its 30th member.<ref>http://www.iea.org/newsroom/news/2018/february/mexico-officially-joins-iea-as-30th-member-country.html</ref>
